707958f-a.text:
Columbian Fusionists Club, 2011 Second Avenue, west side, bewteen 103rd and 104th Streets.  Note the banner for Vito Marcantonio.  Mr. Marcantonio, an intimate friend of Mayor Fiorello H. LaGuardia, was the successful Republican and City Fusion candidate in 1934 for the Congressional seat vacated by LaGuardia on March 4, 1933.
October 17, 1934.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer
